added.title: Just a Little Patience…Yeah…Yeah
added.description: Robin tries to teach the other Titans to have patience.

added.title: Villains in a Van Getting Gelato
added.description: Four of the Titans' greatest villains reminisce about past incidents and recall how the Titans wronged them.

added.title: I Am Chair
added.description: During a stressful trip to the mall, Robin finds peace in a massage chair.

added.title: Bumgorf
added.description: When the Titans realize they have not seen Silkie for a long time, they take turns guessing what happened to him.

added.title: What's Opera, Titans?
added.description: Robin surprises the Titans with a trip to the opera but they soon fall asleep, and all dream about starring in their own operas.

added.title: What We Learned at Camp
added.description: After not receiving participation medals, the Titans must demonstrate what they learned at camp.

added.title: The Great Disaster
added.description: Robin gets amnesia and starts thinking that Hawkman is his mother.

added.title: Panda's Friend
added.description: Panda uses an app to find a friend with whom he has more common with. Soon things take a turn for the worse when the new friend gets too possessive.

added.title: Planet Bears
added.description: A nature documentary follows the Bears through their normal routine, which includes a trip to the grocery store.

added.title: Panda's Art
added.description: Panda paints a portrait of Charlie and it's a hit with his art class. But after an art dealer offers to buy the painting, Panda has to get it back from Charlie.

added.title: Pigeons
added.description: Grizz becomes best buds with a flock of pigeons.

added.title: Panda 2
added.description: Baby Panda happily lives in a closed off environment for study. But when he's given a new friend, Panda 2, his worldview is shaken, which sets him off on a great adventure.

added.title: The Intelligence
added.description: Gumball and Darwin argue with the Internet and make him mad. So mad in fact that he seeks to wipe out humanity and, while doing so, malfunctions! The whole of Elmore is plunged into a time before technology. It's actually pretty nice. Will Gumball and Darwin decide to leave the internet unplugged?

added.title: The Inquisition
added.description: The students of Elmore Junior High find their world turned upside down when the mysterious school superintendent comes to stamp out their cartoonish ways. But who wants to be normal? Certainly not Gumball and Darwin.

added.title: The Hug
added.description: When Darwin taunts Gumball about how predictable he is, Gumball tries to prove he can still surprise his buddy. He thinks greeting a kid he barely knows with a hug will do the trick. He's right but doesn't see the awkward social repercussions of the hug coming.

added.title: The Hero
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are determined to prove to their dad that he is their hero, at any cost!

added.title: The Helmet
added.description: Gumball's magic tinfoil helmet threatens to tear the Watterson family apart!

added.title: Buggin' the Buggs
added.description: Team Tennyson travel to the Chrysalen Institute for some hot yoga and good vibes, only to find that the Bugg Brothers are on vacation, too, but are the sneaky insectoids really on holiday, or just cooking up yet another silly, yet high stakes scheme?

added.title: Baby Buktu
added.description: When attacked in the jungle, Team Tennyson is saved by a toddler who looks eerily similar to Tim Buktu, but when they discover it really is a pint sized version of the nefarious globetrotter, Ben knows there's another threat looming, Nanny Nightmare!

added.title: Mutiny for the Bounty
added.description: While Phil and Grandpa Max tune-up the Omni-Copter, a restless Ben takes the Rustbuggy off road, but when he is suddenly captured by Textrax and the hunter takes the bounty for himself, our hero must not only escape but avoid the wrath of the double-crossed Kraab and Sixsix!

added.title: Buggy Out
added.description: After winning a Sumo Slammers Champion belt, Ben returns to the Rustbucket to find his prize in the arms of Kevin, but when his rival hijacks the Rustbuggy instead, our hero must stop at nothing to get back what's rightfully his!

added.title: Four by Four
added.description: During their visit to Twin City, Ben and Gwen sign up for some Laser Town awesomeness, but when Ben is teamed up with Kevin, the two must overcome their differences if they are to end up on top!

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: While taking refuge from the chilly Creek, Craig and his friends decide to hangout at his house until lunch time!

added.title: Fan or Foe
added.description: When Elder Con comes to the Creek, Craig, Kelsey and JP each have a con experience they'll never forget.

added.title: New Jersey
added.description: After donning a brand new Jersey, JP is recruited by the Hockey Kids! The only way to get JP back is for Craig and Kelsey to hit the ice!

added.title: The Sunflower
added.description: Our Trio makes a new friend in the Creek, but when her pet befalls a tragic fate, Kelsey believes she knows how to help.

added.title: Craig World
added.description: Craig creates an amusement park in the Creek! But when things start to get stale, he vows to make it bigger and better, no matter what it takes!

added.title: Breaking the Ice
added.description: While searching a once unreachable part of the Creek, Craig gets stranded with his longtime rival, Wildernessa!

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: The Cardboard Identity
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon a mysterious bunker made of cardboard beneath the Creek.

added.title: Ancients of the Creek
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP discover an ancient fort that belonged to the first kids in the Creek.

added.title: Life of Pie
added.description: When Izzy, Jude and Owen accidentally bring a pizza to life they do everything they can to help him find a new purpose in life other than being eaten.

added.title: AbaracaDuncan
added.description: When a magic trick goes sideways, Duncan makes a great escape and Harold becomes the target of a Sorcerer Hunt!

added.title: School District 9
added.description: When a career predicting machine tells Owen he has no skills to offer the world, Owen finds a way to prove the machine wrong in the most Owen way possible.

added.title: Aquarium for a Dream
added.description: Gwen tries to convince Chef to tell the class the truth about their pet goldfish.

added.title: Cuttin' Corners
added.description: Duncan, Leshawna and Jude all want corner pieces of Izzy's Birthday Cake… But are they prepared to go to any length to get one?

added.title: Sharing Is Caring
added.description: Courtney refuses to share her valuable collectors item toy with her classmates.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple has to find a way not to lose his best friend.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Apple tries to survive a weekend alone while taking care of Onion's plant.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears while trapped in a pet shop, so they can save French Fry from facing hers.

added.title: Follow Your Dreams
added.description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

added.title: Falafel's in Jail
added.description: Apple & Onion must get Falafel out of jail for a crime he did not commit.

added.title: Ball of Fame
added.description: When Tom and Jerry's antics unearth an autographed baseball, a childhood souvenir of Rick's, he warns Tom to keep his paws off it, or else! Tom attempts to obey but Jerry's got other ideas and the ball gets out of hand. The guys chase the treasured ball all over the neighborhood, recovering it only to lose it again and again.

added.title: Mega-Tom
added.description: Frankenstein turns Tom into a colossus and Tom ends up terrorizing the village mice until Jerry Van Mouseling saves the day.

added.title: Jabberwock
added.description: Tom finds himself trapped inside a Catsylvania bedtime story and fleeing from a furious Jabberwock.

added.title: A Clown Without Pity
added.description: An evil ringmaster recruits Tom to help him snare the Catsylvania mice.

added.title: Duck Sitting
added.description: Tom and Jerry must keep Lil' Quacker safe from Butch and Meathead so that he can testify to a crime in court.

added.title: Dungeon Crawl!
added.description: Having joined forces with the Lowly in their quest to defeat King Vangelis, Cole, Wu, and Vania have to find a way out of the bottom of the mountain, a place said to be inescapable.

added.title: Grief Bringer
added.description: Nya and Kai, who have become the respective leaders of the Munce and Geckles, attempt to unite the tribes in an effort to defeat their mutual enemy, the Skull Sorcerer, who schemes against them.

added.title: Masters Never Quit
added.description: Pursued by a magma monster, Cole, Princess Vania, Wu & the Lowly arrive at a mysterious temple deep in Shintaro Mountain, a temple which was once a training ground for Earth Elementals including Cole's own mother, Lilly!

added.title: The Darkest Hour
added.description: Forced to flee by the arrival of Grief-Bringer, the ninja, the Munce and the Geckles take refuge in the Geckle Strong-Cave. But the bitter feud between Munce and Geckles threatens to tear them apart, just when unity is needed most…when they are about to confront the Skull Sorcerer and Grief-Bringer!

added.title: The Ascent
added.description: Cole, the Lowly, Princess Vania and Wu discover that the stone-mech is fueled by Elemental Power, and attach it to the mine-carts in an effort to blast their way out of the mountain to confront the evil Skull Sorcerer!

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Cuddle Monster
added.description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

added.title: It Grows
added.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: #LeagueOfShadows Part 1
added.description: Under the control of Red Kryptonite, Kara Danvers is brainwashed by rock 'n' roll front man Ra's al Ghul and sent on a mission to purify the world... starting with the terrible music of Karen Beecher's favorite boy band!

added.title: #LeagueOfShadows Part 2
added.description: Under the control of Red Kryptonite, Kara Danvers is brainwashed by rock 'n' roll front man Ra's al Ghul and sent on a mission to purify the world... starting with the terrible music of Karen Beecher's favorite boy band!

added.title: Snarf's Day Off
added.description: Hey everyone, it's Snarf's monthly day off! That's right, this episode follows Snarf as he leaves Cats' Lair to get a needed vacation, by transforming into a normal cat and hanging out with a nice old lady on a farm! But his relaxing day is threatened when Snarf and the nice old lady cross paths with Mumm-Ra!

added.title: Mumm-Ra of Plun-Darr Part 1
added.description: The Thundercats' worst nightmare comes true when their worst enemies, Mumm-Ra and The Mutants, team up after Mumm-Ra acquires The Sword of Plun-Darr!

added.title: Mumm-Ra of Plun-Darr Part 2
added.description: Chaos reigns over Third Earth now that the Mutants and Mumm-Ra control the Cats' Lair! The Thundercats' only hope is to sneak back in and get a super secret weapon Panthro has hidden at the heart of the Lair.

added.title: Mandora's Law
added.description: Tygra creates a bunch of new laws for Third Earth so Mandora can finally arrest the Mutants. Unfortunately the Thundercats are really bad at following their own rules and the Mutants are really good at working around them.

added.title: Thunder Road
added.description: When a crate containing fifty Swords of Omen lands on Third Earth, the ThunderCats rush out in the ThunderTank to find them. Unfortunately The Mutants and Mumm-Ra want those swords too so it's going to be a race to get to them! A wacky race, you might say. We won't say that, but you might.

added.title: Coach Steven
added.description: After seeing Gamet and Amethyst fuse together into the powerful Sugilit - Steven becomes determined to get super strong.

added.title: An Indirect Kiss
added.description: When Amethyst cracks her gemstone, Steven and the Crystal Gems go on a mission to heal her.

added.title: House Guest
added.description: After injuring his leg, Greg comes to live with Steven and unintentionally interferes with Steven's powers.

added.title: Alone Together
added.description: The Gems try to teach Steven to use his fusion powers.

added.title: Full Disclosure
added.description: Steven tries to avoid Connie so he doesn't have to tell her about his most recent harrowing adventure.

added.title: Try Hard
added.description: When the Sky Pirates take Mao Mao and Badgerclops hostage, it's up to Adorabat to save the day.

added.title: Scared of Puppets
added.description: Mao Mao is scared of puppets.

added.title: High Strangeness
added.description: An otherworldly encounter puts Tree Trunks on the trail of a conspiracy in the Candy Kingdom.

added.title: Hall of Egress
added.description: Trapped and alone, Finn must unravel the riddle of the weird cave with no exit.

added.title: Hitman
added.description: The Ice King tries to win Princess Bubblegum over with his love potion.

added.title: Her Parents
added.description: Jake pretends to be a rainicorn in order to make Lady's parents like him.

added.title: Heat Signature
added.description: Marceline messes with Finn and Jake and tells them they're vampires, but maybe this joke has gone too far.

added.title: El silencioso
added.description: Mientras que Lloyd y Harumi se aventuran a lo profundo de "Primeval's Eye" en busca de la tercer máscara Oni, los ninja tratan de arreglar al Bounty y hacer un descubrimiento sorprendente.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Quiet One
added.description: As Lloyd and Harumi venture deep into Primeval's Eye in search of the third Oni Mask, the ninja attempt to fix the Bounty and make a startling discovery.

added.title: Juego de mascaras
added.description: Mientras Lloyd y Harumi buscan el templo Oni para la última máscara, los ninjas son tomados como rehenes y descubren que verdaderas intensiones de la Princesa Harumi.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Game of Masks
added.description: As Lloyd and Harumi search the Oni Temple for the last mask, the ninja are taken hostage and discover Princess Harumi's true intentions.

added.title: Terror llegando
added.description: Los ninjas recurren al comisionado de la policía de Ninjago en un esfuerzo por ayudar a salvar a Lloyd y frustrar los esfuerzos de Harumi de resucitar al malvado Lord Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Dread on Arrival
added.description: The ninja appeal to the police commissioner of Ninjago in an effort to help save Lloyd and thwart Harumi's efforts to resurrect the evil Lord Garmadon.

added.title: Struck by Lightning
added.description: Muscle Man and High Five Ghost get struck by lightning and can't remember each other.

added.title: El verdadero potencial
added.description: Justo cuando los ninjas piensan que han salvado el día, Lord Garmadon regresa a Ninjago, y libera a Harumi, quien lo anima a "alcanzar su verdadero potencial" conquistando lo único que siempre se interpuso en su camino, su hijo, Lloyd.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: True Potential
added.description: Just when the Ninja think they have saved the day, Lord Garmadon returns to Ninjago, and frees Harumi, who encourages him to "achieve his true potential" by conquering the one thing that has always stood in his way, his son, Lloyd.

added.title: Ninjago chico, problemas grandes
added.description: Los ninjas corres a salvar a Lloyd. Un Lord Garmadon más poderoso que nunca, crea una enorme estatua para ayudarlo a gobernar Ninjago y a derrotar a los ninjas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Big Trouble, Little NinjaGo
added.description: The ninja race to save Lloyd, as a more powerful-than-ever Lord Garmadon creates an enormous Colossi to help him rule Ninjago and defeat the ninja.

added.title: The Button
added.description: The guys have to protect a large red button from being pushed.

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: Lift With Your Back
added.description: Rigby wants to prove to Mordecai that he can earn a paycheck from another job.

added.title: La Inteligencia
added.description: La tecnología alcanza el nivel de la inteligencia humana, y luego se vuelve disfuncional cuando imita sus defectos.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Men in Uniform
added.description: The park guys want to keep the park open for business.

added.title: La Inquisicion
added.description: El superintendente escolar Malo visita la Secundaria Elmore para erradicar cualquier conducta caricaturesca.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: Aunt Grandma's back is causing more trouble for Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: La Opera Titan
added.description: Robin sorprende a los demás Titanes con un viaje a la ópera, pero pronto se duermen y sueñan con protagonizar sus propias obras musicales.

added.title: Lo que aprendimos en el campamento
added.description: Después de no recibir sus medallas de participación, los Titanes deben demostrar lo que aprendieron en el campamento.

added.title: El gran desastre
added.description: Robin pierde la memoria y comienza a pensar que Hombre Halcón es su madre.

added.title: Big Fat Alien Wedding
added.description: Ben and Gwen accompany Max to a wedding, which doesn't make Ben particularly happy, especially given the fact he has to wear a tux and learn how to dance. During the wedding it's revealed that the bride's parents are aliens while the groom's family are ex-Plumbers. It turns out the bride's parents are out to sabotage the wedding because of a long lasting feud with the Plumbers, and take action by demonstrating their destructive powers and causing deadly havoc. Ben, Max and Gwen enter the fray and not only save the day, but make sure the ceremony goes on as planned.

added.title: El amigo de panda
added.description: Panda usa una aplicación para encontrar a un amigo con el que tenga más cosas en común. Muy pronto, las cosas dan un giro negativo cuando el nuevo amigo se vuelve demasiado posesivo.

added.title: Planeta osos
added.description: Un documental sobre la naturaleza sigue a los Osos durante su rutina normal, que incluye un viaje a la tienda de comestibles.

added.title: El arte de panda
added.description: Panda pinta un retrato de Charlie que se vuelve un éxito en su clase de arte. Pero cuando un marchante ofrece comprar la pintura, Panda tiene que lograr que Charlie se la devuelva.

added.title: Palomas
added.description: Grizz se hace muy amigo de una bandada de palomas.

added.title: Panda dos
added.description: Panda bebé es un sujeto de estudio que vive feliz en un ambiente aislado. Pero cuando llega Panda 2, un nuevo amigo, su visión del mundo se sacude, lo cual lo lanza a una gran aventura.

added.title: Molestando a los Bichos
added.description: El equipo de Tennyson viaja al Instituto Crisalín en busca de yoga a altas temperaturas y buenas vibraciones, solo para descubrir que los hermanos Bicho también están de vacaciones. Pero ¿los astutos insectoides están realmente de vacaciones, o están tramando otro de sus tontos planes?

added.title: Bebe Baktu
added.description: Cuando es atacado en la jungla, el equipo Tennyson es salvado por un niño que se parece inquietantemente a Tim Buktu, pero cuando descubren que realmente es una versión en miniatura del infame trotamundos, Ben sabe que se avecina otra amenaza, Nanny Nightmare!

added.title: Paseo en Buggy
added.description: Después de ganar un cinturón como campeón de Luchadores de Sumo, Ben regresa al Rustbucket y encuentra su premio en los brazos de Kevin. Pero cuando su rival secuestra el Rustbuggy, inuestro héroe no debe detenerse ante nada para recuperar lo que le pertenece legítimamente!

added.title: Cuatro por Cuatro
added.description: Durante su visita a Ciudad Gemelos, Ben y Gwen se inscriben en una competencia de laser-tag. Pero cuando Ben se une a Kevin, los dos deben superar sus diferencias si quieren terminar en la cima.

added.title: Huelga por el Botin
added.description: Mientras Phil y el abuelo Max afinan el Omni-Copter, Ben, inquieto, saca el Rustbuggy de la carretera. Pero cuando de repente es capturado por Tetrax, nuestro héroe no solo debe escapar, sino también evitar la ira de los traicioneros Kraab y SeiSeis.

added.title: Cambio de Temporada
added.description: Cuando nuestros héroes regresan de sus vacaciones, K.O. se horroriza al descubrir que las cosas cambiaron.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Seasons Change
added.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

added.title: Big Tick
added.description: A giant alien tick that sucks planets dry, lands on Earth with the sole purpose of destroying the planet and only a new alien hero can stop it.

added.title: Mal Radical
added.description: Cuando llega un nuevo reemplazo, K.O. y Dendy deciden que necesitan recuperar a su antiguo profesor.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: The So-Bad-Ical
added.description: When a new substitute shows up, KO and Dendy decide they need to get their old teacher back.

added.title: Are You Talking to Tree?
added.description: When the tree inside the RV begins talking to Uncle Grandpa, he must convince the gang that he's not going crazy.

added.title: Apointa a la Plaza
added.description: Cuando la plaza se infesta de pegote, P.O.I.N.T. llega para contener la situación.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Point to the Plaza
added.description: When a Gloop infestation takes over the plaza, Point arrives to contain the situation.

added.title: Red Action to the Future
added.description: When Red Action is called to the future for an epic battle, Enid is unsure of what to do.

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: Sneaky Peeky
added.description: After missing out on a chance to see the premiere of the new Robofrog movie trailer, the trio devises a plan to sneak into the theater and catch a glimpse before anyone else. However, when they accidentally damage the reel, they're forced to fix it or fess up!

added.title: Game Show
added.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

added.title: Super Black Friday
added.description: After being forced to work on a holiday, KO, Rad and Enid take a stand.

added.title: Mystery Girl
added.description: After Clarence and pals call random numbers as a prank, Clarence ends up connecting with a girl and they strike up a friendship. But will this long distance phone pal last?

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Jeff's Secret
added.description: When Clarence discovers a new quirk about his friend, Jeff begs Clarence not to tell. Can Clarence resist the urge to expose Jeff's secret to the whole school?

added.title: Ancianos de arroyo
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP descubren una fortaleza antigua que les perteneció a los primeros niños del bosque.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Super Dia de Ofertas
added.description: Cuando los obligan a trabajar en un día festivo, KO, Rad y Enid se pronuncian en contra de la medida.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Accion Roja al Futuro
added.description: Cuando convocan a Acción Roja a una batalla épica en el futuro, Enid no está segura de lo que debe hacer.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La casa de munecas embrujada
added.description: Craig y sus amigos descubren que los persigue una muñeca aterradora y su casa de muñecas embrujada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La identidad de carton
added.description: Craig y sus amigos se topan con un refugio subterráneo hecho de cartón debajo del bosque.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Capullos de Rosa
added.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

added.title: Voleibol
added.description: Steven está decidido a ayudar a la Perla original de Diamante Rosa para sanar la cicatriz en su rostro.

added.title: La pecera de los suenos
added.description: Gwen trata de convencer a Chef de que le diga a la clase la verdad sobre su pececito dorado.

added.title: Conquistando torres
added.description: Duncan, Leshawna y Jude quieren una pieza de esquina del pastel de cumpleaños de Izzy, pero, ¿están preparados para hacer cualquier cosa por conseguir uno?

added.title: Compartir es querer
added.description: Courtney se niega a compartir su valioso juguete de coleccionista con sus amigos.

added.title: Afraid of the Dark
added.description: When UG helps a little girl who is afraid of the dark, he convinces her there's nothing to be afraid of but their imaginations.  But when their imaginations prove to be pretty terrifying, they go on a quest to turn on the lights.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: Nueva Mascota
added.description: Después de que Chata les dijera que no pueden tener una mascota, Vic y Val adoptan un lagarto salvaje, sin conocer sus propiedades mágicas, y deciden mantenerlo en secreto para que Chata no se entere.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val le guarda rencor a Vic, lo cual atrae sin querer a un malvado cadejo, una bestia mitológica parecida a un lobo.

added.title: Frenemy
added.description: When the coolest girl in school befriends the girls, she charms them into becoming her accomplices in a series of adventurous crimes.

added.title: Crece
added.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: Rush to Greatness
added.description: Rush puts his new battle upgrades to the test in a battle with Wave Man.

added.title: Swish
added.description: Namagem attacks Mega Man using a variety of powers, revealing that they both can replicate schematics. However, Namagem can carry more than three at a time! The true beginning of the mysterious villain's arc begins here.

added.title: Minus Mini
added.description: When Mega Mini is kidnapped by Blasto Woman, Mega Man must track down his missing partner without the full use of his own systems.

added.title: A Cut Above
